### ABSTRUCT ###

Maxwell project was developed in scope of a PhD research to porovide 
heigh efficient numerical evaluation tool. Research topic is trancient 
field radiation in nonlinear trancient nonstationary medium from arditrary
sourse. The tool allows to compute and plot electromagnetic field with 
arbitrary radiator and compare result with pre-defined solution.

Source code is wrote within ISO c++14 standard and POSIX comatibility. 
Build system is only one Makefile with several available options. 
There are 'test', 'maxwell' and 'debug' options. Code containce paralel 
calculations on std::threads with data access control on std::mutex.

Source code and build systems supports GNU/Linux, MacOS and BSD operation 
systems. Development dependency is limited by C++ development stack and
X11 development package. Folowing OS list is recomended for development 
process, the system is tested on the list:

- GNU/Linux Ubuntu 16.04 LTE x86_64 (GNU GCC version 5.4.0 20160607)
- MacOS Sierra 10.12.5 x86_64 (Apple LLVM version 8.1.0)

### NOTES ###

lux et veritas

Наука сама по себе деградирует. Чем выше уровень научного прогресса тем
сильнее само-деградация. По этому для роста древа знаний человечество 
нуждается в новых инструментах. Только появление новых инструментов может 
сдержать эту деградцию.  

Generalized Gaussian Quadrature Rules For Systems of Arbitrary Functions

### UBUNTU INSTALL ###

~ $ sudo apt-get install build-essential cmake git
~ $ sudo apt-get install libx11-dev
~ $ git clone https://server/maxwell.git
~ $ make gnuplot gnump test
~ $ ./build/test
~ $ make -j4 maxwell
~ $ ./build/maxwell --help
~ $ ./build/maxwell --model 1 --arg 1.5 90
~ $ ./build/maxwell --model 5

### USEFULL DEBUG COMANDS

~ $ make clean
~ $ make list

~ $ du -h ./build/maxwell
~ $ ls -lh ./build/maxwell
~ $ file ./build/maxwell
~ $ stat -x ./build/maxwell
~ $ nm -D libgmp.so | grep __gmpf_init

~ $ cat <> maxwell.conf | sed '/\(^FLOAT_BITRATE =\).*/ s//\1$(TERMS)/'
~ $ date && nice -n 10 ./build/gnuplot --conf PATH --model NUM && date

